The paper analyzes the use of Twitter as a source of external links for webometric analysis, which involves the study of web-based information and its impact on society. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including social networks (cs.SI), information retrieval (cs.IR), social and information networks (cs.SOC), digital libraries (cs.DL), and cybersecurity (cs.CYBER). The paper specifically focuses on the use of Topsy search engine to compile tweets related to 200 universities, which involves data mining and information retrieval techniques. Therefore, cs.SI and cs.IR are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.SOC and cs.DL, which also involve network analysis and data mining. cs.CYBER is less likely but still relevant due to the potential security and privacy implications of using social media data for webometric analysis.
